  "prompt": "How do I have to pay the installments once I bought something through krazybee?",
  "response": "When you purchase an item through Krazybee, you typically have to follow a structured payment plan for your installments. Here\u2019s a general overview of how the payment process usually works:\n\n1. **Understanding the Plan**: After making a purchase, you\u2019ll receive details about the installment plan, including the amount owed, interest rates (if any), and due dates.\n\n2. **Payment Methods**: You can usually make payments through various methods such as:\n   - Bank transfers (NEFT/RTGS)\n   - UPI payments\n   - Credit or debit card payments\n   - Payment through the Krazybee app or website\n\n3. **Due Dates**: Ensure you are aware of the due dates for each installment. Payments are generally made monthly, and it\u2019s crucial to stick to these dates to avoid penalties.\n\n4. **Automated Payments**: Some users might opt for automatic debit arrangements, where the payment is automatically deducted from their bank account. This can help in ensuring timely payments.\n\n5. **Tracking Payments**: Use the Krazybee app or website to keep track of your payment history and outstanding balance.\n\n6. **Late Payments**: Be mindful of the consequences of late payments, which could include additional fees or impacts on your credit score.\n\n7. **Customer Support**: If you have specific questions or issues regarding payments, it's always best to contact Krazybee\u2019s customer support for precise information.\n\nMake sure to read the terms and conditions provided at the time of purchase for any details specific to your agreement.",
